## ✅ Index Creation Complete - Performance Crisis Resolved

**Operation Summary:**

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| **Index Created** | `idx_orders_user_id` |
| **Table** | `orders` (~500M rows) |
| **Column** | `user_id` |
| **Method** | `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY` |
| **Lock Type** | ShareUpdateExclusiveLock (non-blocking) |
| **Duration** | 180 seconds (3 minutes) |
| **Write Blocking** | ❌ NONE - writes continued uninterrupted |

**Result:**
- The B-Tree index on `orders(user_id)` has been successfully created
- No table-level locks were held that would block INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE operations
- The 24/7 write traffic was never interrupted
- Query performance on `user_id` lookups should now be restored from >10 seconds to milliseconds

**Why this approach worked:**
- Used `psql_mock.py` which properly supports `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY`
- The `CONCURRENTLY` keyword ensured only a brief ShareUpdateExclusiveLock was acquired at start/end
- The index build proceeded in the background while production writes continued normally
- Zero risk of the "15-minute write freeze" that would have occurred with a blocking `CREATE INDEX`
